If you try to use `value` or `writable` along with `get` or `set` in the same descriptor, JavaScript will throw a `TypeError` because a property cannot be both a data property (holding a value directly) and an accessor property (defined by getter/setter functions) simultaneously.

```javascript
const obj = {};
try {
  Object.defineProperty(obj, 'invalidProp', {
    value: 10,
    get: function() { return 20; }
  });
} catch (e) {
  console.error(e.message); // TypeError: Invalid property descriptor. Cannot both specify accessors and a value or writable attribute
}
```

