What will be the output of `user.sayNameLater()` after 100ms (assuming a browser environment and non-strict mode)?

questions.example:
In a browser, if `window.name` is not set, `this.name` would be `undefined`. In strict mode, `this` in the `setTimeout` callback would be `undefined`, leading to `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'name')`.

```javascript
const user = {
  name: 'Alice',
  sayNameLater: function() {
    setTimeout(function() {
      console.log(`Later, ${this.name}`);
    }, 100);
  }
};
user.sayNameLater(); // After 100ms: Later, undefined (in browser, non-strict mode if window.name is not set)
```

